@{
    Layout = "_Layout";
}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>FAQ - Library Management</title>

    <style>
        /* Global Styles */
        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #f8f9fa;
            color: #343a40;
        }

        .faq-container {
            max-width: 1000px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 40px 20px;
        }

        .faq-title {
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 48px;
            font-weight: 700;
            color: #000000; 
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 2px;
        }

        /* FAQ Item */
        .faq-item {
            background-color: red;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            overflow: hidden;
            transition: all 0.3s ease-in-out;
        }

            .faq-item:hover {
                transform: scale(1.05);
                box-shadow: 0 6px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
                background-color: #e0e0e0; /* Tukar latar belakang kepada kelabu apabila hover */
            }

        .faq-question {
            padding: 20px;
            font-size: 20px;
            font-weight: 600;
            color: #000000; /* Tukar warna biru kepada hitam */
            background-color: #f1f1f1;
            border-top-left-radius: 8px;
            border-top-right-radius: 8px;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
        }

            .faq-question:hover {
                background-color: grey; /* Tukar latar belakang kepada biru apabila hover */
                color: #fff; /* Tukar teks kepada putih semasa hover */
            }

        .faq-answer {
            padding: 20px;
            font-size: 16px;
            color: #555;
            background-color: #fff;
            display: none;
            border-bottom-left-radius: 8px;
            border-bottom-right-radius: 8px;
        }

            /* Show answer with transition */
            .faq-answer.open {
                display: block;
            }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="faq-container">
        <h1 class="faq-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">
                <h4>What is Library ManagementAPI ?</h4>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>
                    LibraryManagementAPI is an advanced solution for managing library resources, inc
                    luding books, student records, and borrowed materials. It simplifies library 
                    management processes and enhances the overall user experience.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <br/>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">
                <h4>How can I manage my library resources?</h4>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>To manage your library resources effectively, you can use a 
                    library management system (LMS) to catalog and track books, student records, 
                    and borrowed materials. This system allows you to streamline borrowing and returns, 
                    maintain up-to-date records, and ensure resources are easily accessible to users. 
                    Additionally, regularly updating your inventory and automating tasks like reminders for overdue items can 
                    help keep everything organized and efficient.</p>
            </div>
        </div>


        <br />

        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">
                <h4>Can I customize the library system?</h4>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>Yes, the library system can be customized to meet 
                    the specific needs of your library. You can modify features such as cataloging, 
                    borrowing processes, user roles, and reporting based on your requirements. 
                    Whether you're looking to add custom fields, integrate with other systems, or personalize the user interface, 
                    customization options are available to ensure the system aligns with your library’s operations.</p>
            </div>
        </div>


        <br />

        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">
                <h4>How do I get support?</h4>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>If you need support, you can reach out to our customer service 
                    team via email at support@librarymanagementapi.com or through our support hotline at 012-3456789. 
                    You can also access our help center for troubleshooting guides,
                    FAQs, and tutorials. Our team is available to assist you with any issues you may encounter, 
                    and we're committed to ensuring your experience with the system is smooth and efficient.</p>
            </div>
        </div>


        <br />

        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">
                <h4>Is the library system available online?</h4>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>Yes, the library system is available online. 
                    You can access it from any device with an internet connection,
                    allowing you to manage library resources, check out books, and track your borrowed materials anytime, 
                    anywhere. Simply log in through the web portal or mobile app to get started.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>

    <script>
        document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function () {
            const faqItems = document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item');

            faqItems.forEach(item => {
                const question = item.querySelector('.faq-question');
                const answer = item.querySelector('.faq-answer');

                question.addEventListener('click', () => {
                    // Toggle answer visibility
                    answer.classList.toggle('open');

                    // Optionally, close other answers when one is opened
                    faqItems.forEach(otherItem => {
                        if (otherItem !== item) {
                            otherItem.querySelector('.faq-answer').classList.remove('open');
                        }
                    });
                });
            });
        });
    </script>

</body>
</html>
